description: Sunday mornings spent thinking about the rat race, relationships, dreams. We all seem to be in such a hurry to find some kind of meaning in this chaos. I put down my over-priced coffee when this little cat caught my eye. She was busy just being a cat, not a worry in a world. It reminded me of how insignificant all the material things are, how fleeting time is. It was time to just; be.
